Compressed sensing has been shown to be able to estimate sparse or compressible signals from incomplete measurements [17], [18]. Consider a signal x in RN. x is called sparse if most elements of x are zero. Similarly, x is compressible if most elements of x are near zero. Specifically, x is S-sparse if ||x||0≤S, where S is a positive integer and ||·||p is the ℓp-norm operator defined as(10)where p is non-negative integers. Let us further define the set of S-sparse vectors:(11)Then, a vector x′ in RN can be approximated by a vector x in ΣS, and the approximation error of x′ in ℓp-norm, σS(x′)p, is(12)where inf(·) is the infimum operator. If σS(
